{
  "stem": "26111.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because I was suffering the consequences in a way, since I was being sent to a German-- to a German school and having the experiences that I just mentioned.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So there was a bit-- little less enthusiasm about that and less understanding about that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's where the conflict came in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I really had to establish myself, even at that early age, as someone that had certain ideas, that had certain ideals as well.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was in search of them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And Habonim was one of the-- and Zionism in general was one of the places where I went in search of it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Synagogue was another one.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the atmosphere of the synagogue immediately, it was a rather-- architecturally, a rather imposing and, and pleasant building.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And it was there that I-- there, there was a-- the kind of-- the kind of atmosphere communicated itself to me that is supposed to come to you in synagogues, churches, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The builders of the synagogue would have been very pleased.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It came about, I'm afraid, in a negative way, no less strong.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It came about through the experiences that I just mentioned, which made me understand my 'apart-ness' was the only way that I could-- that I could [BACKGROUND NOISE] explain the behavior of the other children, of the masters, of the world around me.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was starting to read newspapers [LAUGHS] at that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I knew what was going on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It, it, it sounds very different from the typical high school child in, in, in, in America or probably in England, too.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, but under those circumstances, one, one grows up very fast.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had many friends.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The friends had children.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I don't recall even that it was the children that-- through whom I got this information.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
